comment:
* Description of the response of a setup data call connection request.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: LINK_STATUS_INACTIVE
variables.comment: Indicates the data connection is inactive.

variables.name: LINK_STATUS_DORMANT
variables.comment: Indicates the data connection is active with physical link dormant.

variables.name: LINK_STATUS_ACTIVE
variables.comment: Indicates the data connection is active with physical link up.

variables.name: HANDOVER_FAILURE_MODE_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: * Data handover failure mode is unknown.

variables.name: HANDOVER_FAILURE_MODE_LEGACY
variables.comment:
* Perform fallback to the source data transport on data handover failure using
     * the legacy logic, which is fallback if the fail cause is
     * {@link DataFailCause#HANDOFF_PREFERENCE_CHANGED}.

variables.name: HANDOVER_FAILURE_MODE_DO_FALLBACK
variables.comment: * Perform fallback to the source data transport on data handover failure.

variables.name: HANDOVER_FAILURE_MODE_NO_FALLBACK_RETRY_HANDOVER
variables.comment:
* Do not perform fallback to the source data transport on data handover failure.
     * Framework will retry setting up a new data connection by sending
     * {@link DataService#REQUEST_REASON_HANDOVER} request to the underlying {@link DataService}.

variables.name: HANDOVER_FAILURE_MODE_NO_FALLBACK_RETRY_SETUP_NORMAL
variables.comment:
* Do not perform fallback to the source transport on data handover failure.
     * Framework will retry setting up a new data connection by sending
     * {@link DataService#REQUEST_REASON_NORMAL} request to the underlying {@link DataService}.

variables.name: RETRY_DURATION_UNDEFINED
variables.comment:
* Indicates that data retry duration is not specified. Platform can determine when to
     * perform data setup appropriately.

variables.name: PDU_SESSION_ID_NOT_SET
variables.comment: * Indicates that the pdu session id is not set.

methods.name: public int getCause()
methods.comment: * @return Data call fail cause. {@link DataFailCause#NONE} indicates no error.

methods.name: public int getSuggestedRetryTime()
methods.comment:
* @return The suggested data retry time in milliseconds. 0 when network does not
     * suggest a retry time (Note this is different from the replacement
     * {@link #getRetryDurationMillis()}).
     *
     * @deprecated Use {@link #getRetryDurationMillis()} instead.

methods.name: public long getRetryDurationMillis()
methods.comment:
* @return The network suggested data retry duration in milliseconds as specified in
     * 3GPP TS 24.302 section 8.2.9.1.  The APN associated to this data call will be throttled for
     * the specified duration unless {@link DataServiceCallback#onApnUnthrottled} is called.
     * {@code Long.MAX_VALUE} indicates data retry should not occur.
     * {@link #RETRY_DURATION_UNDEFINED} indicates network did not suggest any retry duration.

methods.name: public int getId()
methods.comment: * @return The unique id of the data connection.

methods.name: public int getLinkStatus()
methods.comment: * @return The link status

methods.name: public int getProtocolType()
methods.comment: * @return The connection protocol type.

methods.name: public String getInterfaceName()
methods.comment: * @return The network interface name (e.g. "rmnet_data1").

methods.name: public List<LinkAddress> getAddresses()
methods.comment: * @return A list of addresses of this data connection.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getDnsAddresses()
methods.comment:
* @return A list of DNS server addresses, e.g., "192.0.1.3" or
     * "192.0.1.11 2001:db8::1". Empty list if no dns server addresses returned.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getGatewayAddresses()
methods.comment:
* @return A list of default gateway addresses, e.g., "192.0.1.3" or
     * "192.0.1.11 2001:db8::1". Empty list if the addresses represent point to point connections.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getPcscfAddresses()
methods.comment:
* @return A list of Proxy Call State Control Function address via PCO (Protocol Configuration
     * Option) for IMS client.

methods.name: public int getMtu()
methods.comment:
* @return MTU (maximum transmission unit) in bytes received from network. Zero or negative
     * values means network has either not sent a value or sent an invalid value.
     * @deprecated For IRadio 1.5 and up, use {@link #getMtuV4} or {@link #getMtuV6} instead.

methods.name: public int getMtuV4()
methods.comment:
* This replaces the deprecated method getMtu.
     * @return MTU (maximum transmission unit) in bytes received from network, for IPv4.
     * Zero or negative values means network has either not sent a value or sent an invalid value.

methods.name: public int getMtuV6()
methods.comment:
* @return MTU (maximum transmission unit) in bytes received from network, for IPv6.
     * Zero or negative values means network has either not sent a value or sent an invalid value.

methods.name: public int getHandoverFailureMode()
methods.comment: * @return The data handover failure mode.

methods.name: public int getPduSessionId()
methods.comment: * @return The pdu session id

methods.name: public Qos getDefaultQos()
methods.comment:
* @return default QOS of the data connection received from the network
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public List<QosBearerSession> getQosBearerSessions()
methods.comment:
* @return All the dedicated bearer QOS sessions of the data connection received from the
     * network.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public NetworkSliceInfo getSliceInfo()
methods.comment: * @return The slice info related to this data connection.

methods.name: public List<TrafficDescriptor> getTrafficDescriptors()
methods.comment: * @return The traffic descriptors related to this data connection.

methods.name: public int getNetworkValidationStatus()
methods.comment:
* Return the network validation status that was initiated by {@link
     * DataService.DataServiceProvider#requestNetworkValidation}
     *
     * @return The network validation status of data connection.
